What is the aim when you do code review?
    1) Add value to System:
           Maintainability
           Operations
           Scalability
           Performance
    2) Add value to People
           Help them learn new things
    3) Add to Best Practices:
            Identify common mistakes

When do you do code review ?
    New developer joins the team?
    New technology change is being implemented?

What are the good practices in doing Code Reviews?
    1) Ideally Pair Programming Reviews
         Fixing comments directly discussing with developers
    2) Use static analysis tools - SONAR
    3) Quality of Junit is a great guide to the quality of system
    4) Check Readability of code

What are the things you look for in:
    1) Architecture:
        Frameworks choice
        Communication with other systems
        Testability
        Components
        Reuse

    2) Design:
        Interactions between classes
        Layer Responsibilities
        OOPS principles
        Unit Tests